Day 20 - 3 days left until gold medal, 0 days until single digits.

Congrats soldiers! There are now 10 days left, by technicality we're just saying that it's single digits now so for those who have made it this far you've done the NNN legion a great service! Now then, some motivation to keep y'all occupied.

You've gone through 20, entire, days without failing. Where most would fail on day 1, or hell even the day 7 massacre you still live. Even if it's just barely, you are still in and you always will be as long as we stick together. Failing now will mean you have wasted 20 days worth of effort, most people will have to wait 11 months to get here again and yet you're still pulling through. If you've made it this far, what's stopping you from going the rest of the way?

As always, thank you soldiers for all of the support on these posts! I read & upvote every single message, and it warms my heart to see that I'm able to support soldiers in a time of need and am their NNN run's savior. Just as I help support & motivate all of you, you help support & motivate me. Thanks again soldiers, when this is over I'm gonna miss y'all. See ya tomorrow, never give up! o7

Capt. Hector's Log book. November 20th, 1887:

I get my ship fixed up, hired the crew to replace the old one, and I decided to stay on land for a few days to rest, recover, and recuperate. I'm in desperate need to silence the screams that rung within my head every time I close my eyes.

I make my way to the Ladybones Road. The stench of brimstone is thick in the air, for this is the place where devils congregate. Rumors of a restaurant so good they "make your worries go away" is what I heard. Of course, this is not literal, but perhaps those devils know something that we don't, and I have nothing to lose, so might as well.

I am in front of the restaurant, Dante's Grill. Let's see if the rumors are true.

I prayed to Salt, Storm, and Stone that I will survive this voyage, for the deep dark zee is unforgiving.
